    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a pristine example of rotary engineering. This vehicle features the original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, delivering a linear power band with a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis maintains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, supported by all-aluminum double-wishbone suspension components that minimize unsprung weight. Every vacuum line, solenoid, and actuator in the 'rat's nest' has been inspected and remains in peak operating condition, showing no signs of thermal degradation. The exterior retains its factory-spec finish with zero oxidation, while the interior plastics and upholstery are free from the common delamination or UV damage associated with this era. This is a collector-grade specimen for the technical purist.",
